1
00:00:00,240 --> 00:00:01,400
[Disclaimer:
All depicted events are fictional

2
00:00:01,440 --> 00:00:02,600
and for entertainment purposes only;
viewer discretion is advised]

3
00:00:14,800 --> 00:00:18,530
[Love Upon a Time Series]

4
00:00:18,880 --> 00:00:20,880
Do you believe in multiple lifetimes?

5
00:00:23,900 --> 00:00:24,570
Master Klao!

6
00:00:24,600 --> 00:00:25,560
- What?!
- Master!

7
00:00:25,710 --> 00:00:26,710
Where am I?

8
00:00:27,060 --> 00:00:28,410
I too have been pondering

9
00:00:28,600 --> 00:00:30,200
the circumstances that brought you here.

10
00:00:31,600 --> 00:00:33,190
How the hell did I end up here?

11
00:00:33,220 --> 00:00:34,440
What happened to me?!

12
00:00:37,480 --> 00:00:38,980
[Love Upon a Time Series]

13
00:01:49,800 --> 00:01:52,300
[Love Upon a Time Series]

14
00:01:57,340 --> 00:01:59,759
Take a look at the student
who is sleeping over there.

15
00:02:00,910 --> 00:02:04,280
Maybe he's already traveled back in time to
either the Sukhothai or Ayutthaya period.

16
00:02:11,500 --> 00:02:14,570
Students, what are common methods
for main characters

17
00:02:15,360 --> 00:02:18,340
to travel back in time

18
00:02:18,500 --> 00:02:20,160
and then return to the present?

19
00:02:20,700 --> 00:02:22,040
Through a mirror.

20
00:02:22,740 --> 00:02:25,410
Drowning and being transported
into a body in a different era.

21
00:02:25,450 --> 00:02:27,960
Seeing one's past life
after wearing a traditional costume.

22
00:02:28,320 --> 00:02:29,160
Mm.

23
00:02:30,140 --> 00:02:32,000
Those are interesting answers.

24
00:02:32,460 --> 00:02:36,000
But sometimes, drifting off to sleep,

25
00:02:36,900 --> 00:02:38,079
passing out,

26
00:02:38,700 --> 00:02:40,970
or being knocked out by an accident

27
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:43,940
can make someone travel back in time.

28
00:02:44,329 --> 00:02:46,280
When it comes to traveling back in time,

29
00:02:46,310 --> 00:02:50,120
death is considered the starting point.

30
00:02:50,560 --> 00:02:54,160
It's about dying
and traveling to a different realm,

31
00:02:54,620 --> 00:02:57,079
then being reincarnated as someone else.

32
00:03:20,340 --> 00:03:22,130
Hey, go away.

33
00:03:22,160 --> 00:03:23,600
I want to return to the present.

34
00:03:29,610 --> 00:03:31,160
I'm telling you to go away!

35
00:04:21,160 --> 00:04:23,160
This guy again.

36
00:04:23,520 --> 00:04:24,800
Why am I still here?

37
00:04:25,060 --> 00:04:27,060
I'm stuck in a loop.

38
00:04:27,100 --> 00:04:30,320
Why didn't I die and return to the present
like the professor said?

39
00:04:32,040 --> 00:04:33,170
Sterilized cloth, posthaste!

40
00:04:33,200 --> 00:04:34,120
Yes, my Lord.

41
00:04:35,880 --> 00:04:36,909
Gosh, you.

42
00:04:36,940 --> 00:04:39,180
It's just a guy who got soaked.
No need to yell.

43
00:04:44,040 --> 00:04:44,880
As you requested, my Lord.

44
00:05:07,700 --> 00:05:08,880
Really?

45
00:05:09,300 --> 00:05:12,840
Why is he patting me dry?

46
00:05:20,780 --> 00:05:22,620
That tickles.

47
00:05:27,220 --> 00:05:29,800
But if I open my eyes now, I'll be screwed.

48
00:05:35,090 --> 00:05:36,640
Fetch your Master fresh attire,

49
00:05:37,100 --> 00:05:39,159
and summon all servants to the hall.

50
00:05:41,470 --> 00:05:45,360
Tarry no longer,
for my indulgence has its limits.

51
00:05:46,260 --> 00:05:46,960
Yes, Lord.

52
00:05:49,580 --> 00:05:50,440
Wait.

53
00:05:50,690 --> 00:05:53,780
"Fetch me fresh attire"?
I'm going to be naked?

54
00:05:54,180 --> 00:05:55,640
Hey, don't you dare.

55
00:05:55,730 --> 00:05:56,350
Don't do it.

56
00:05:56,380 --> 00:05:57,380
Don't!

57
00:06:04,390 --> 00:06:05,080
Hey.

58
00:06:18,160 --> 00:06:19,120
Wretched!

59
00:06:19,150 --> 00:06:20,050
You son of a rogue!

60
00:06:20,080 --> 00:06:21,610
Father and son alike, wretched both!

61
00:06:21,640 --> 00:06:23,280
- Bastard.
- You son of a rogue!

62
00:06:23,310 --> 00:06:25,090
You shall never prosper, Klao!

63
00:06:25,120 --> 00:06:27,770
- Father and son alike, wretched both!
- The likes of you shall never prosper!

64
00:06:27,800 --> 00:06:28,520
Vile thing!

65
00:06:28,550 --> 00:06:31,120
- Scum!
- The likes of you shall never prosper, Klao!

66
00:06:31,150 --> 00:06:32,560
Whither do you think to escape me!!

67
00:06:39,460 --> 00:06:40,159
Oh...

68
00:06:40,960 --> 00:06:42,040
A dream within a dream.

69
00:06:42,480 --> 00:06:45,000
Am I dreaming, or is this real?

70
00:06:55,600 --> 00:06:57,120
What is the matter, Master Klao?

71
00:06:58,810 --> 00:07:00,440
Okay, that hurts.

72
00:07:00,900 --> 00:07:02,160
I'm not dreaming.

73
00:07:13,120 --> 00:07:15,260
So I've traveled back in time.

74
00:07:15,760 --> 00:07:19,240
The costumes... the manor...
I'm in the Ayutthaya period, right?

75
00:07:19,860 --> 00:07:21,720
I drowned and passed out,

76
00:07:22,080 --> 00:07:23,480
but I didn't return to the present.

77
00:07:24,360 --> 00:07:25,520
So that's not my way out.

78
00:07:27,260 --> 00:07:28,480
I want my iPad.

79
00:07:28,980 --> 00:07:29,980
I need Wi-Fi.

80
00:07:30,250 --> 00:07:32,170
I want to ask an AI,

81
00:07:32,200 --> 00:07:34,040
"How do I go back to the present?"

82
00:07:37,360 --> 00:07:38,360
Wait...

83
00:07:39,900 --> 00:07:43,320
Who the hell dressed me up?!

84
00:07:45,290 --> 00:07:47,460
Dear Klao's arrival
heralds not the conclusion.

85
00:07:49,680 --> 00:07:51,909
You suffered him to slip away,

86
00:07:51,940 --> 00:07:54,000
unbeknownst to any soul.

87
00:07:55,470 --> 00:07:58,280
Upon his return, you offered him no succor,
whilst he sank to the depths.

88
00:07:58,970 --> 00:07:59,920
Chuay.

89
00:08:01,950 --> 00:08:04,880
Have you discerned where he has gone?

90
00:08:05,840 --> 00:08:07,570
Before he vanished,

91
00:08:07,860 --> 00:08:10,000
he was last seen at the riverside market.

92
00:08:10,220 --> 00:08:13,080
And he has been absent ever since.

93
00:08:18,900 --> 00:08:21,310
Henceforth, provide him
with your utmost devotion

94
00:08:21,940 --> 00:08:23,720
and maintain a vigilant watch over him,

95
00:08:23,880 --> 00:08:25,320
especially you, Chuay.

96
00:08:25,620 --> 00:08:27,640
Should any further misfortune befall him,

97
00:08:28,220 --> 00:08:29,840
the caning shall be yours.

98
00:08:34,960 --> 00:08:37,000
I fear a bitter cold has taken hold of him.

99
00:08:37,400 --> 00:08:39,320
Summon the Curer at once.

100
00:08:39,960 --> 00:08:40,409
Yes, Lord.

101
00:08:40,440 --> 00:08:41,480
- Yes, Lord.
- Yes, my Lord.

102
00:08:42,980 --> 00:08:43,890
Make way.

103
00:08:57,360 --> 00:08:59,040
I am well aware of your wakefulness,

104
00:09:02,370 --> 00:09:03,900
having heard every word
I spoke behind closed doors.

105
00:09:08,460 --> 00:09:10,440
Well, you yelled
as if the house were on fire.

106
00:09:13,680 --> 00:09:14,680
Forgive me.

107
00:09:16,120 --> 00:09:17,290
Do you wish to return to slumber?

108
00:09:18,840 --> 00:09:19,840
I'm good.

109
00:09:21,980 --> 00:09:22,680
Hey...

110
00:09:23,340 --> 00:09:24,280
By the way,

111
00:09:24,840 --> 00:09:26,600
did you put on new clothes for me?

112
00:09:28,200 --> 00:09:28,840
Indeed.

113
00:09:29,300 --> 00:09:30,300
What stirs your concern?

114
00:09:31,600 --> 00:09:34,280
No, you can't just change
someone's clothes.

115
00:09:34,880 --> 00:09:36,480
I didn't give my consent either.

116
00:09:40,780 --> 00:09:41,800
What has caused this discord?

117
00:09:44,620 --> 00:09:46,960
It was ever my hands
that clothed you in your youth.

118
00:09:47,420 --> 00:09:49,560
Am I now a stranger in your eyes?

119
00:09:53,880 --> 00:09:55,640
Well, you are a stranger to me...

120
00:09:56,420 --> 00:09:58,480
Whether this be a lapse of memory

121
00:09:58,740 --> 00:10:00,400
or the harboring of some silent grievance,

122
00:10:00,570 --> 00:10:02,200
never repeat such displays of conduct.

123
00:10:02,800 --> 00:10:05,440
Voice your concerns, should any arise.

124
00:10:07,720 --> 00:10:08,790
Forsake not your life.

125
00:10:26,690 --> 00:10:27,950
This way, Curer.

126
00:10:27,980 --> 00:10:29,480
Waste no moment, Curer,

127
00:10:29,600 --> 00:10:30,840
for time is fleeting.

128
00:10:33,320 --> 00:10:34,600
There is no cause for such haste.

129
00:10:34,860 --> 00:10:36,560
I am led to believe he is hale and hearty,

130
00:10:36,770 --> 00:10:38,680
merely adrift in a sea of delusions.

131
00:10:55,500 --> 00:10:56,440
Thee?!

132
00:10:57,380 --> 00:10:58,380
Whoa!

133
00:10:59,560 --> 00:11:00,480
Thee!

134
00:11:02,450 --> 00:11:03,810
Hey, Thee!

135
00:11:03,840 --> 00:11:05,130
- Seize Klao at once!
- Thee!

136
00:11:05,160 --> 00:11:06,130
He has gone mad!

137
00:11:06,160 --> 00:11:08,020
Hey, don't do this, man!

138
00:11:09,800 --> 00:11:10,560
Master Klao.

139
00:11:19,540 --> 00:11:21,040
You traveled through time to save me,

140
00:11:21,260 --> 00:11:22,960
or are you pulling my leg?

141
00:11:36,240 --> 00:11:37,060
Thee.

142
00:11:37,860 --> 00:11:38,920
You've got the guts.

143
00:11:39,200 --> 00:11:40,800
You always have what it takes.

144
00:11:42,690 --> 00:11:44,360
I know your family's rich,

145
00:11:44,700 --> 00:11:46,560
but I didn't expect you to go overboard.

146
00:11:47,150 --> 00:11:50,480
At first,
I thought they were filming a series.

147
00:11:51,140 --> 00:11:53,100
But when I looked around,
there were no cameras.

148
00:11:53,900 --> 00:11:54,840
I've figured it out.

149
00:11:55,510 --> 00:11:57,920
You're providing me
with an immersive experience, right?

150
00:12:04,600 --> 00:12:05,640
Sheesh.

151
00:12:06,340 --> 00:12:08,040
I knew it.

152
00:12:08,070 --> 00:12:10,070
I saw you signaling.

153
00:12:10,740 --> 00:12:12,270
I saw it.

154
00:12:13,160 --> 00:12:14,480
You guys are busted.

155
00:12:17,220 --> 00:12:18,360
Well played, guys.

156
00:12:20,340 --> 00:12:21,760
He suffers not from the wild, Phop,

157
00:12:22,780 --> 00:12:24,190
but from the spirits he has consumed.

158
00:12:26,580 --> 00:12:27,800
I shall provide the remedy.

159
00:12:31,880 --> 00:12:32,720
The remedy?

160
00:12:35,380 --> 00:12:36,160
Hey.

161
00:12:36,920 --> 00:12:38,000
What are you doing?!

162
00:12:38,640 --> 00:12:41,160
Expect a severe purging,

163
00:12:41,300 --> 00:12:42,740
yet the remedy shall bring relief.

164
00:12:43,100 --> 00:12:45,680
It shall restore to him
his lost coherence and dignity.

165
00:12:47,560 --> 00:12:48,680
What are you doing?!

166
00:12:48,860 --> 00:12:50,360
What the hell are you doing to me?!

167
00:12:51,180 --> 00:12:53,530
Spirits transmute a gentleman
into a vessel of madness.

168
00:12:54,000 --> 00:12:55,630
Take this remedy at once, Klao.

169
00:12:56,240 --> 00:12:57,560
Your condition shall improve.

170
00:12:57,580 --> 00:12:59,990
Look at you.
I'm gonna tell Pun about this.

171
00:13:00,260 --> 00:13:02,080
And stop calling me Klao already.

172
00:13:11,500 --> 00:13:13,320
It tastes like shit.

173
00:13:14,090 --> 00:13:15,750
What did you just feed me?

174
00:13:25,980 --> 00:13:27,280
Worry not,

175
00:13:28,080 --> 00:13:29,560
for his recovery is assured.

176
00:13:30,620 --> 00:13:31,880
Are you quite certain, Jom?

177
00:13:33,380 --> 00:13:35,560
It appears his condition
is in further decline.

178
00:13:39,530 --> 00:13:40,930
The remedy takes hold.

179
00:13:42,340 --> 00:13:44,400
The expulsion is but the first step.

180
00:13:55,360 --> 00:13:57,490
Does your skepticism remain, Phop?

181
00:14:00,660 --> 00:14:01,920
Does it not strike you as strange

182
00:14:02,940 --> 00:14:05,320
that he so adamantly denies
his own identity,

183
00:14:06,640 --> 00:14:08,290
yet calls you by another name?

184
00:14:13,140 --> 00:14:14,200
I concur.

185
00:14:15,420 --> 00:14:16,320
It is indeed most peculiar.

186
00:14:17,360 --> 00:14:19,010
Where did he acquire these names?

187
00:14:19,860 --> 00:14:22,160
They are entirely foreign to my ears.

188
00:14:23,360 --> 00:14:24,950
By what name did he address you?

189
00:14:30,700 --> 00:14:32,080
He regarded me

190
00:14:32,880 --> 00:14:34,640
with an unfamiliar eye.

191
00:14:37,420 --> 00:14:39,040
A stark contrast to how he was
when he saw you.

192
00:14:39,740 --> 00:14:41,320
This only serves...

193
00:14:44,000 --> 00:14:44,900
to deepen my suspicions.

194
00:14:49,080 --> 00:14:51,880
I believe he remains clouded
by the spirits.

195
00:14:53,000 --> 00:14:54,280
Cast aside your fears,

196
00:14:55,480 --> 00:14:57,480
lest they erode your reason.

197
00:14:59,000 --> 00:14:59,680
Oh.

198
00:15:00,040 --> 00:15:00,920
Oh, Master.

199
00:15:05,640 --> 00:15:06,480
Master Klao...

200
00:15:15,440 --> 00:15:16,800
Grant him respite,

201
00:15:18,460 --> 00:15:20,320
and forbid him from all further indulgence.

202
00:15:21,400 --> 00:15:23,760
In due time,
he shall be restored to his true self.

203
00:15:34,140 --> 00:15:36,440
Even Thee...

204
00:15:38,340 --> 00:15:39,920
Whatever.

205
00:15:41,780 --> 00:15:44,240
I need to find a way back.

206
00:15:45,920 --> 00:15:49,370
Students, what are common methods
for main characters

207
00:15:49,400 --> 00:15:50,840
to return to the present?

208
00:15:51,220 --> 00:15:52,640
Through a mirror.

209
00:15:52,780 --> 00:15:55,140
Drowning and being transported
into a body in a different era.

210
00:15:55,300 --> 00:15:58,080
Seeing one's past life
after wearing a traditional costume.

211
00:15:59,080 --> 00:16:00,000
Drowning.

212
00:16:03,800 --> 00:16:04,520
A mirror.

213
00:16:08,800 --> 00:16:09,800
A traditional costume.

214
00:16:10,640 --> 00:16:12,000
The Master's mind has once again wandered.

215
00:16:12,520 --> 00:16:14,850
May a star fall this night.

216
00:16:14,880 --> 00:16:18,080
I shall offer prayers
for his swift restoration.

217
00:16:18,240 --> 00:16:19,280
Sadhu.

218
00:16:20,540 --> 00:16:21,960
Tonight...

219
00:16:22,540 --> 00:16:23,770
A starfall!

220
00:16:23,800 --> 00:16:25,560
I nearly fell, Master!

221
00:16:29,540 --> 00:16:30,380
Yes.

222
00:16:31,700 --> 00:16:33,320
Before I passed out,

223
00:16:34,220 --> 00:16:35,720
I saw a starfall.

224
00:16:36,540 --> 00:16:37,240
Hey, you!

225
00:16:39,400 --> 00:16:41,760
This humble servant is named Chuay,
not You, Master.

226
00:16:42,840 --> 00:16:43,840
Oh, whatever.

227
00:16:47,160 --> 00:16:47,960
Right now,

228
00:16:49,040 --> 00:16:50,640
where's that scary-looking guy?

229
00:16:55,480 --> 00:16:56,570
The...

230
00:16:56,600 --> 00:16:57,800
The deadpan-looking guy.

231
00:16:57,880 --> 00:16:59,850
The Lord...

232
00:16:59,880 --> 00:17:00,850
or whatever he's called.

233
00:17:00,880 --> 00:17:02,160
He has taken his leave

234
00:17:02,680 --> 00:17:04,680
and returned to
High Lord Pichayabhakdi's manor.

235
00:17:05,740 --> 00:17:06,720
So...

236
00:17:07,819 --> 00:17:09,760
Can you take me back to the woods,

237
00:17:12,480 --> 00:17:13,960
to where you found me, Chuay?

238
00:17:14,980 --> 00:17:16,200
Please help me out, Chuay.

239
00:17:17,200 --> 00:17:18,359
That cannot be done, Master.

240
00:17:18,760 --> 00:17:20,089
The Lord has commanded me

241
00:17:20,119 --> 00:17:21,119
to...

242
00:17:21,520 --> 00:17:23,760
prevent any attempt at departure.

243
00:17:24,240 --> 00:17:25,240
Should I disobey,

244
00:17:25,720 --> 00:17:27,680
I would be caned unto my doom.

245
00:17:51,220 --> 00:17:52,480
They cannot be opened, Master.

246
00:17:53,740 --> 00:17:55,680
They have been barred from the outside.

247
00:17:56,320 --> 00:17:58,450
We are both confined to these quarters

248
00:17:58,480 --> 00:18:00,360
until the Lord returns.

249
00:18:02,400 --> 00:18:03,800
Unbelievable!

250
00:18:04,620 --> 00:18:07,680
This is basically solitary confinement.

251
00:18:08,600 --> 00:18:10,120
I'm not shackled by his love!

252
00:18:10,620 --> 00:18:12,040
Get me out of here now!

253
00:18:14,020 --> 00:18:14,800
Hey!

254
00:18:16,920 --> 00:18:18,560
They cannot be made to open, Master.

255
00:18:29,160 --> 00:18:29,880
Fine.

256
00:18:30,900 --> 00:18:32,000
You'll see.

257
00:19:07,320 --> 00:19:08,720
I did warn you, Master.

258
00:19:09,520 --> 00:19:10,800
The doors cannot be opened.

259
00:19:11,260 --> 00:19:12,840
They have been barred from the outside.

260
00:19:17,000 --> 00:19:17,720
Fine.

261
00:19:29,840 --> 00:19:32,000
Oh, good heavens!

262
00:19:33,000 --> 00:19:34,280
A fall from such a height

263
00:19:34,580 --> 00:19:36,880
would certainly shatter
one's bones to dust.

264
00:19:37,560 --> 00:19:38,760
The thought of such an antic...

265
00:19:39,720 --> 00:19:40,720
sends a chill through my marrow.

266
00:19:57,080 --> 00:19:58,120
Oh, I'm done.

267
00:20:10,280 --> 00:20:12,080
I can't think of anything.

268
00:20:12,820 --> 00:20:14,080
My Master,

269
00:20:14,600 --> 00:20:16,560
pray tell me.

270
00:20:16,780 --> 00:20:18,960
Is your condition

271
00:20:19,320 --> 00:20:21,040
the result of an indulgence in opium?

272
00:20:28,640 --> 00:20:29,560
If I tell you,

273
00:20:31,380 --> 00:20:33,080
will you take me to the woods?

274
00:20:35,080 --> 00:20:36,320
I cannot, Master.

275
00:20:38,160 --> 00:20:39,400
Master,

276
00:20:41,260 --> 00:20:43,480
was your absence
due to an indulgence in opium?

277
00:20:48,240 --> 00:20:49,680
If I tell you,

278
00:20:51,280 --> 00:20:56,600
you will take me to the woods, right?

279
00:20:56,920 --> 00:20:58,480
It cannot be done, Master.

280
00:21:00,260 --> 00:21:02,160
I think enough has been said.

281
00:21:02,920 --> 00:21:04,200
My master

282
00:21:04,740 --> 00:21:06,200
would not succumb to the allure of opium.

283
00:21:07,420 --> 00:21:09,080
There is a remedy for spirits,

284
00:21:10,060 --> 00:21:11,520
but for the opium

285
00:21:13,240 --> 00:21:15,120
even the Curer has none.

286
00:21:17,720 --> 00:21:18,760
You mean Thee?

287
00:21:20,840 --> 00:21:22,200
I once had back pain.

288
00:21:22,760 --> 00:21:24,160
I asked him to buy me some plasters,

289
00:21:24,860 --> 00:21:26,800
but he came back
with a bag of plaster mix instead!

290
00:21:30,240 --> 00:21:30,960
The Curer...

291
00:21:38,360 --> 00:21:39,240
Master?

292
00:21:39,820 --> 00:21:41,040
What troubles you so?

293
00:21:41,480 --> 00:21:42,320
A stomachache.

294
00:21:44,000 --> 00:21:44,760
Master.

295
00:21:46,160 --> 00:21:48,800
It feels like my tummy's gonna explode.

296
00:21:49,520 --> 00:21:51,970
A stomachache that could burst one's belly?

297
00:21:52,000 --> 00:21:52,720
Perhaps...

298
00:21:53,640 --> 00:21:55,320
Are you afflicted
with abdominal tuberculosis?

299
00:21:55,760 --> 00:21:57,290
Yes. Abdominal tuberculosis!

300
00:21:57,320 --> 00:21:59,810
Ab-dominoes and everything. Argh!

301
00:21:59,840 --> 00:22:00,730
Get the Curer.

302
00:22:00,760 --> 00:22:02,210
Summon the Curer for me.

303
00:22:02,240 --> 00:22:03,280
Yes, Master.

304
00:22:04,040 --> 00:22:05,410
It hurts. I can't.

305
00:22:05,440 --> 00:22:07,200
My stomach's going to burst!

306
00:22:07,680 --> 00:22:08,520
Cuckoo.

307
00:22:09,380 --> 00:22:10,300
Cuckoo!

308
00:22:11,360 --> 00:22:12,240
Cuckoo.

309
00:22:13,220 --> 00:22:13,800
Cuckoo!

310
00:22:37,240 --> 00:22:38,060
Cuckoo.

311
00:22:40,200 --> 00:22:41,030
Cuckoo!

312
00:22:45,340 --> 00:22:46,440
Cuckoo!!

313
00:22:52,980 --> 00:22:53,980
Quite a rascal.

314
00:23:08,920 --> 00:23:10,000
But I'm worse.

315
00:23:27,940 --> 00:23:28,760
Ow!

316
00:23:42,120 --> 00:23:42,960
This way.

317
00:23:43,160 --> 00:23:44,520
Make haste, I beg you.

318
00:23:45,040 --> 00:23:46,410
What is it, Chuay?

319
00:23:46,440 --> 00:23:47,730
His arrival was but recent,

320
00:23:47,760 --> 00:23:49,480
yet you seek the Curer
only after nightfall?

321
00:23:50,000 --> 00:23:51,090
You again.

322
00:23:51,120 --> 00:23:53,760
Do people in the old days
have nothing better to do?

323
00:23:54,040 --> 00:23:55,200
It is Master Klao, my Lord.

324
00:23:55,720 --> 00:23:57,590
Such is his distress that he recoils.

325
00:23:57,620 --> 00:23:59,040
I believe he suffers from
abdominal tuberculosis.

326
00:23:59,850 --> 00:24:01,400
Could such a disease be possible?

327
00:24:01,920 --> 00:24:03,560
His restless spirit
showed no sign of waning.

328
00:24:05,320 --> 00:24:06,800
Under whose watchful eye does he rest?

329
00:24:11,980 --> 00:24:13,920
Chuay, you have been deceived by him.

330
00:24:27,360 --> 00:24:28,280
Klao.

331
00:24:30,240 --> 00:24:31,800
What brings you to these shadows?

332
00:24:42,240 --> 00:24:42,880
Pun!

333
00:24:43,540 --> 00:24:44,960
Yes. I'm safe now.

334
00:24:48,480 --> 00:24:49,240
Pun.

335
00:24:50,120 --> 00:24:51,240
What are you doing here?

336
00:24:52,040 --> 00:24:52,610
Gosh...

337
00:24:52,640 --> 00:24:54,260
You know what's happening, don't you?

338
00:24:57,560 --> 00:24:58,480
Klao...

339
00:24:59,420 --> 00:25:01,080
Jom's words were true.
You have lost your wits.

340
00:25:04,080 --> 00:25:05,200
Hey, Pun.

341
00:25:05,560 --> 00:25:07,200
No, don't do me like this.

342
00:25:07,640 --> 00:25:09,360
Klao, it pains me.

343
00:25:10,320 --> 00:25:11,200
Jom!

344
00:25:11,960 --> 00:25:12,960
Where are you?!

345
00:25:13,280 --> 00:25:14,200
Jom!

346
00:25:21,760 --> 00:25:22,880
Good morning.

347
00:25:23,760 --> 00:25:24,800
Oh, Nakun?

348
00:25:25,160 --> 00:25:26,210
Have you eaten yet?

349
00:25:26,240 --> 00:25:27,200
I'm starving.

350
00:25:27,800 --> 00:25:29,650
Nakun, try this.

351
00:25:29,680 --> 00:25:30,720
It's mint-flavored, a new one.

352
00:25:31,900 --> 00:25:32,640
If you don't mind...

353
00:25:36,320 --> 00:25:37,760
- How is it?
- Gosh...

354
00:25:38,050 --> 00:25:38,980
Refreshing breath,

355
00:25:39,340 --> 00:25:41,000
nice and clean.

356
00:25:43,180 --> 00:25:44,600
What kind of prank is this, Thee?

357
00:25:47,120 --> 00:25:47,880
Thee.

358
00:25:48,560 --> 00:25:50,350
Stop pulling pranks on Nakun.

359
00:25:50,380 --> 00:25:51,560
This isn't funny at all.

360
00:25:52,980 --> 00:25:54,080
Eat it yourself.

361
00:25:54,540 --> 00:25:58,280
He mocks me for liking mint chocolate.

362
00:26:01,760 --> 00:26:02,600
Uh...

363
00:26:03,240 --> 00:26:04,280
It's fine, Pun.

364
00:26:04,860 --> 00:26:05,640
This is nothing.

365
00:26:06,120 --> 00:26:08,460
He always does stuff like this.

366
00:26:09,880 --> 00:26:11,440
Come on, Pun.

367
00:26:11,520 --> 00:26:13,010
You're mad at me like I pranked you.

368
00:26:13,040 --> 00:26:14,040
I'll eat it. Here.

369
00:26:14,520 --> 00:26:15,640
Hey, don't.

370
00:26:15,840 --> 00:26:16,560
It's fine.

371
00:26:17,280 --> 00:26:18,160
It's nothing.

372
00:26:18,540 --> 00:26:19,850
Well, enjoy.

373
00:26:19,880 --> 00:26:20,560
I just ate some.

374
00:26:23,480 --> 00:26:25,040
Yeah, eat up!

375
00:26:25,680 --> 00:26:26,740
- Look at him.
- You...

376
00:26:27,060 --> 00:26:28,080
You're still mad at me?

377
00:26:28,540 --> 00:26:30,160
Pun doesn't pull pranks on others.

378
00:26:33,800 --> 00:26:34,730
If this is really him,

379
00:26:34,760 --> 00:26:36,160
he wouldn't be deceiving me.

380
00:26:38,480 --> 00:26:39,360
Why?

381
00:26:39,940 --> 00:26:41,680
Traveling through time isn't enough?

382
00:26:42,080 --> 00:26:45,240
Why is it someone who looks like
my friend and fraternity brother?

383
00:26:53,140 --> 00:26:53,800
Klao.

384
00:26:53,940 --> 00:26:54,960
Return to the manor at once.

385
00:26:55,780 --> 00:26:56,600
Let go!

386
00:26:57,760 --> 00:26:59,280
I told you I'm not Klao!

387
00:27:00,600 --> 00:27:01,960
Stop calling me by that name already!

388
00:27:03,600 --> 00:27:04,570
Master Klao!

389
00:27:05,000 --> 00:27:05,880
Master.

390
00:27:06,080 --> 00:27:06,800
Trouble no further.

391
00:27:07,880 --> 00:27:09,120
Allow him his solitude.

392
00:27:09,660 --> 00:27:11,680
Leave him to the quiet counsel
of his own thoughts.

393
00:27:13,180 --> 00:27:14,120
I shall attend to him shortly.

394
00:27:28,930 --> 00:27:29,690
Of course.

395
00:27:30,170 --> 00:27:31,550
Why would there be a starfall?

396
00:27:32,370 --> 00:27:33,960
It doesn't happen
every night, does it?

397
00:27:35,410 --> 00:27:37,040
I won't get to return home, will I?

398
00:27:38,570 --> 00:27:40,040
Will my mom be surprised?

399
00:27:40,580 --> 00:27:42,640
What about the real Thee and Pun?
How will they be?

400
00:27:52,520 --> 00:27:53,840
You're here to drag me back?

401
00:27:56,920 --> 00:27:58,280
I am here for the sake of companionship.

402
00:28:31,000 --> 00:28:32,560
Draw your breath slowly,

403
00:28:34,040 --> 00:28:35,360
or you will faint.

404
00:29:19,320 --> 00:29:19,960
Hey.

405
00:29:21,420 --> 00:29:22,640
Who were those two?

406
00:29:23,800 --> 00:29:25,280
Jom and Kaew,

407
00:29:26,660 --> 00:29:28,600
companions since our youth.

408
00:29:34,240 --> 00:29:35,360
You...

409
00:29:35,620 --> 00:29:36,880
You're not lying, are you?

410
00:29:46,240 --> 00:29:48,520
Deception has no place in my heart
when I speak to you.

411
00:29:56,520 --> 00:29:57,400
Thank you.

412
00:29:59,560 --> 00:30:00,480
Thanks.

413
00:30:28,760 --> 00:30:29,880
Rest now.

414
00:30:30,960 --> 00:30:32,800
Long and undisturbed repose
is what is required.

415
00:30:33,800 --> 00:30:34,920
Fret not,

416
00:30:35,780 --> 00:30:38,000
for you shall return to your senses
in no time.

417
00:30:43,520 --> 00:30:44,480
Can I ask you something?

418
00:30:59,280 --> 00:31:00,240
Where are we?

419
00:31:04,360 --> 00:31:05,560
This is the small manor,

420
00:31:06,800 --> 00:31:09,480
situated on
the estate of High Lord Pichayabhakdi,

421
00:31:11,240 --> 00:31:12,640
my father's.

422
00:31:14,560 --> 00:31:16,160
Why does your mind fail to recall this?

423
00:31:17,520 --> 00:31:18,460
And...

424
00:31:19,240 --> 00:31:20,440
what province?

425
00:31:25,240 --> 00:31:26,080
Province?

426
00:31:29,360 --> 00:31:30,440
What city?

427
00:31:32,340 --> 00:31:33,760
Is it in Bangkok or what?

428
00:31:39,320 --> 00:31:40,880
Do you speak of...

429
00:31:42,640 --> 00:31:43,720
Phra Nakhon?

430
00:31:45,940 --> 00:31:47,080
Phra Nakhon...

431
00:31:48,400 --> 00:31:50,920
Phra Nakhon Si Ayutthaya?

432
00:31:52,660 --> 00:31:53,360
No.

433
00:31:55,380 --> 00:31:57,640
Ayothaya Si Ram Thep Nakhon.

434
00:31:58,580 --> 00:31:59,160
And...

435
00:32:00,560 --> 00:32:01,480
Day?

436
00:32:02,680 --> 00:32:03,640
What day is it?

437
00:32:04,840 --> 00:32:05,640
Sunday.

438
00:32:06,600 --> 00:32:07,360
What month

439
00:32:09,680 --> 00:32:10,400
and year?

440
00:32:10,960 --> 00:32:12,320
Year Eight of the Decennial Cycle.

441
00:32:13,580 --> 00:32:15,840
1038 of the Lesser Era.

442
00:32:16,180 --> 00:32:17,240
The Year of the Dragon.

443
00:32:18,600 --> 00:32:19,800
The Second Lunar Month.

444
00:32:21,040 --> 00:32:22,120
The First Waxing Moon.

445
00:32:23,360 --> 00:32:24,160
Sunday.

446
00:32:33,140 --> 00:32:35,400
The reign of King Songtham.

447
00:32:37,560 --> 00:32:38,330
[King Songtham]

448
00:32:38,360 --> 00:32:41,080
Who is King Songtham?

449
00:32:41,280 --> 00:32:44,800
I just know King Naresuan and King Narai.
[Royal Chronicles of Ayutthaya Kingdom]

450
00:32:45,240 --> 00:32:46,890
Lesser Era? The Decennial Cycle?
[The 13 Kings of the Suphannaphum Dynasty]

451
00:32:46,920 --> 00:32:48,170
What year in our modern calendar

452
00:32:48,200 --> 00:32:49,640
is this Lesser Era?

453
00:32:50,740 --> 00:32:51,950
See, Nakun?!

454
00:32:51,980 --> 00:32:53,080
This is why you failed the exam!

455
00:32:53,400 --> 00:32:55,520
Why didn't you study hard?!

456
00:32:56,720 --> 00:33:00,320
I've really traveled back
to the Ayutthaya period, haven't I?

457
00:33:00,720 --> 00:33:02,800
Around 300-400 years ago.

458
00:33:04,720 --> 00:33:05,440
Ow!

459
00:33:07,510 --> 00:33:08,680
Have you sustained any injuries?

460
00:33:23,320 --> 00:33:24,240
Hey, what are you doing?

461
00:33:48,360 --> 00:33:50,200
I'm okay. I'm fine.

462
00:33:50,230 --> 00:33:51,720
Remain still for a moment.

463
00:34:15,710 --> 00:34:16,800
Do men of this age

464
00:34:17,590 --> 00:34:19,820
actually look this handsome?

465
00:34:22,820 --> 00:34:23,320
Hey!

466
00:34:23,639 --> 00:34:24,760
No, no, no, no.

467
00:34:25,130 --> 00:34:26,800
He's 400 years older than me.

468
00:34:27,139 --> 00:34:28,150
He may be good-looking,

469
00:34:28,179 --> 00:34:29,960
but he's like
my great-great-great ancestors!

470
00:34:37,400 --> 00:34:38,000
Klao?

471
00:34:40,260 --> 00:34:42,000
Is it that your memory of me has faded,

472
00:34:43,880 --> 00:34:45,360
or do you harbor grievances against me?

473
00:34:56,800 --> 00:34:57,480
No matter.

474
00:35:01,160 --> 00:35:02,240
It matters not now.

475
00:35:04,260 --> 00:35:05,160
Rest,

476
00:35:06,420 --> 00:35:07,960
and adhere to
the Curer's medicinal instructions,

477
00:35:10,520 --> 00:35:12,120
and you shall recover.

478
00:36:10,560 --> 00:36:11,440
Let's say.

479
00:36:11,690 --> 00:36:12,800
Let's just say...

480
00:36:13,320 --> 00:36:15,280
I've really traveled back
to the Ayutthaya period.

481
00:36:15,780 --> 00:36:16,800
The question is...

482
00:36:17,040 --> 00:36:18,240
Why me?

483
00:36:18,930 --> 00:36:20,240
Why here?

484
00:36:22,790 --> 00:36:24,440
What promise did you make, and to whom?

485
00:36:25,060 --> 00:36:26,440
Someone from the past
awaits its fulfillment.

486
00:36:27,560 --> 00:36:29,480
Why the hell
do I have to get into this faculty?

487
00:36:30,100 --> 00:36:31,880
Can we go back in time and change this?

488
00:36:32,200 --> 00:36:34,000
What if time, as we know it,

489
00:36:34,140 --> 00:36:35,920
doesn't move linearly?

490
00:36:36,060 --> 00:36:38,280
It loops back,

491
00:36:38,680 --> 00:36:39,680
becoming a cycle.

492
00:36:39,940 --> 00:36:41,160
This suggests that

493
00:36:41,780 --> 00:36:43,840
the concepts of past and future lives
might actually exist.

494
00:36:44,780 --> 00:36:45,680
Traveling back in time

495
00:36:46,420 --> 00:36:48,640
and becoming myself in my past life?

496
00:36:49,380 --> 00:36:50,040
No way.

497
00:36:50,880 --> 00:36:51,960
That's insane.

498
00:36:52,700 --> 00:36:53,640
It's impossible, right?

499
00:36:54,520 --> 00:36:56,120
That's way too much like fiction.

500
00:37:04,400 --> 00:37:06,640
Alright. If I can't go back right now,

501
00:37:06,860 --> 00:37:08,400
I guess I have to become Klao.

502
00:37:09,520 --> 00:37:11,760
I guess you're Klao now, Nakun!

503
00:37:33,280 --> 00:37:34,480
Are you awake from your slumber?

504
00:37:47,460 --> 00:37:49,240
Would you refresh yourself, Master?

505
00:37:51,740 --> 00:37:52,520
Sure.

506
00:37:53,340 --> 00:37:55,770
Does the bathroom have a shower

507
00:37:55,800 --> 00:37:57,720
or a bathtub?

508
00:38:10,040 --> 00:38:13,560
There are no bathrooms
in the Ayutthaya period?!

509
00:38:22,620 --> 00:38:23,200
Ah!

510
00:38:25,200 --> 00:38:26,680
So cold! I refuse.

511
00:38:26,840 --> 00:38:28,480
I won't shower no matter what.

512
00:38:33,040 --> 00:38:33,760
Chuay.

513
00:38:35,160 --> 00:38:38,280
Can you heat up the water for me?

514
00:38:41,240 --> 00:38:43,240
Please?

515
00:38:43,400 --> 00:38:45,280
Master has gone mad,
yet he shall recover...

516
00:38:46,080 --> 00:38:48,040
Master has gone mad,
yet he shall recover.

517
00:38:48,240 --> 00:38:49,960
Master has gone mad,
yet he shall recover...

518
00:38:50,840 --> 00:38:52,840
Master has gone mad,
yet he shall recover.

519
00:38:53,100 --> 00:38:54,080
Master has gone mad,

520
00:38:54,360 --> 00:38:55,480
yet he shall recover.

521
00:38:55,960 --> 00:38:56,560
Chuay.

522
00:38:57,810 --> 00:38:58,440
Yes, Master?

523
00:38:58,900 --> 00:38:59,720
What is this?

524
00:38:59,800 --> 00:39:00,760
Is it a makeup brush?

525
00:39:18,790 --> 00:39:19,640
Master.

526
00:39:20,720 --> 00:39:23,720
The trousers you wear,
are they from the Farangi?

527
00:39:24,560 --> 00:39:25,240
Oh.

528
00:39:25,700 --> 00:39:26,680
You mean my boxers?

529
00:39:27,020 --> 00:39:28,160
Uh...

530
00:39:28,900 --> 00:39:31,680
Yes, they're from Farangi.

531
00:39:31,780 --> 00:39:32,800
Oh, but...

532
00:39:33,540 --> 00:39:35,120
Don't let anyone touch them.

533
00:39:35,220 --> 00:39:36,960
Don't let anyone wash them either.

534
00:39:37,140 --> 00:39:38,810
They're extremely important.

535
00:39:38,840 --> 00:39:39,960
It's my personal belonging,

536
00:39:40,260 --> 00:39:41,080
and it was expensive.

537
00:39:41,920 --> 00:39:43,000
It's also a one-off.

538
00:39:43,560 --> 00:39:44,200
Yes, Master.

539
00:39:44,900 --> 00:39:48,640
I shall not lay my hands on your "boxers."

540
00:39:52,900 --> 00:39:54,040
Gosh...

541
00:39:55,120 --> 00:39:56,240
Alright.

542
00:40:00,040 --> 00:40:01,760
Hair curls.

543
00:40:02,480 --> 00:40:04,120
Check out those commas.

544
00:40:04,210 --> 00:40:05,920
It's the Korean style,

545
00:40:07,160 --> 00:40:07,880
you know?

546
00:40:09,180 --> 00:40:09,760
Come on.

547
00:40:10,240 --> 00:40:11,760
I'm craving breakfast.

548
00:40:12,930 --> 00:40:13,520
Ha!

549
00:40:17,920 --> 00:40:20,440
Master has gone mad,
yet he shall recover.

550
00:40:20,640 --> 00:40:22,400
Master has gone mad,
yet he shall recover...

551
00:40:25,780 --> 00:40:26,640
Await me, Master.

552
00:40:28,740 --> 00:40:29,660
Your rice, Master.

553
00:40:30,620 --> 00:40:31,560
Thank you.

554
00:40:33,820 --> 00:40:35,080
Feast, Master.

555
00:40:41,780 --> 00:40:42,440
Uh...

556
00:40:44,380 --> 00:40:45,720
Where are my spoon and fork?

557
00:40:46,160 --> 00:40:47,840
You want me to eat with my hands?

558
00:40:56,800 --> 00:40:57,640
Here, Master.

559
00:40:59,480 --> 00:41:00,240
Yes, Master...

560
00:41:01,320 --> 00:41:02,160
Yes, Master.

561
00:41:28,960 --> 00:41:31,720
Sai poured her whole heart
into this course.

562
00:41:32,240 --> 00:41:33,120
Indeed, Master.

563
00:41:34,340 --> 00:41:35,840
Your name is Sai?

564
00:41:36,720 --> 00:41:37,480
Yes, Master.

565
00:41:38,040 --> 00:41:39,080
She is my beloved.

566
00:41:41,620 --> 00:41:42,280
Your beloved?

567
00:41:46,540 --> 00:41:48,000
Chuay, how old are you?

568
00:41:48,220 --> 00:41:49,840
Why did you get a wife so quickly?

569
00:41:50,060 --> 00:41:51,040
This is nothing strange.

570
00:41:51,640 --> 00:41:54,060
My peers have already founded
their own lineages.

571
00:41:55,200 --> 00:41:56,040
And...

572
00:41:56,480 --> 00:41:57,400
Klao....

573
00:41:57,820 --> 00:41:58,400
Sorry.

574
00:42:00,200 --> 00:42:00,960
What about me?

575
00:42:01,960 --> 00:42:03,040
Master Klao...

576
00:42:04,260 --> 00:42:05,800
You have even forgotten about…

577
00:42:06,820 --> 00:42:07,720
I have one?

578
00:42:08,960 --> 00:42:09,740
No, Master.

579
00:42:10,940 --> 00:42:11,680
What a relief.

580
00:42:16,040 --> 00:42:17,520
Does no trace of it remain?

581
00:42:18,530 --> 00:42:19,440
Well...

582
00:42:20,780 --> 00:42:21,960
I'm starting to recall some of it now.

583
00:42:23,220 --> 00:42:25,010
Grant us your questions,

584
00:42:25,040 --> 00:42:27,000
for we are both ready to answer.

585
00:42:27,420 --> 00:42:28,570
Sai and I

586
00:42:28,600 --> 00:42:30,400
shall aid you
in regaining memories, Master.

587
00:42:33,520 --> 00:42:34,650
Well...

588
00:42:37,530 --> 00:42:38,960
That deadpan Lord...

589
00:42:40,300 --> 00:42:41,120
is he taken?

590
00:42:47,280 --> 00:42:49,190
Our Lord is a gracious

591
00:42:49,220 --> 00:42:50,530
and generous soul,

592
00:42:50,560 --> 00:42:52,790
much like High Lord Pichayabhakdi,

593
00:42:52,820 --> 00:42:53,880
his father.

594
00:42:54,760 --> 00:42:55,890
He is devoid of arrogance,

595
00:42:55,920 --> 00:42:58,240
treating even the lowliest
with unwavering respect.

596
00:42:58,740 --> 00:43:00,960
He bears a most refined composure,

597
00:43:01,660 --> 00:43:03,400
befitting his striking visage.

598
00:43:25,240 --> 00:43:25,900
By the way...

599
00:43:26,400 --> 00:43:27,560
This Lord...

600
00:43:27,980 --> 00:43:29,080
How old is he?

601
00:43:29,860 --> 00:43:31,480
He is your elder by a year.

602
00:43:32,160 --> 00:43:33,920
He will reach his 21st year
in the course of this cycle.

603
00:43:35,140 --> 00:43:36,320
21...

604
00:43:37,440 --> 00:43:40,080
Handsome, with a wealthy father...

605
00:43:40,840 --> 00:43:44,000
He's not old by the standards of this era.

606
00:43:45,120 --> 00:43:47,080
I guess he's married, right?

607
00:43:47,520 --> 00:43:49,760
He has yet to establish
a household of his own.

608
00:43:50,440 --> 00:43:51,160
Really?

609
00:43:51,560 --> 00:43:52,920
Despite his good looks,

610
00:43:53,720 --> 00:43:55,000
he's still not married?

611
00:43:56,420 --> 00:43:57,760
Such is not the case, Master.

612
00:43:58,980 --> 00:44:00,920
A lord of such striking beauty

613
00:44:01,140 --> 00:44:04,840
holds half the maidens of the capital
in longing for his hand.

614
00:44:18,060 --> 00:44:18,970
Desired by many,

615
00:44:19,000 --> 00:44:21,160
he is yet moved by none.

616
00:44:23,840 --> 00:44:25,000
Hm...

617
00:44:25,320 --> 00:44:27,080
He's not keen on commitment, is he?

618
00:44:27,440 --> 00:44:28,320
He is not, Master.

619
00:44:28,980 --> 00:44:31,000
He takes no liking to any maiden,

620
00:44:31,540 --> 00:44:33,360
nor does he seek

621
00:44:33,540 --> 00:44:34,720
the company of women of the night.

622
00:44:40,080 --> 00:44:40,920
Is he gay?

623
00:44:42,720 --> 00:44:43,680
No, Master.

624
00:44:44,180 --> 00:44:45,400
He is not gray.

625
00:44:46,040 --> 00:44:47,200
He is sharp, not dull.

626
00:44:49,460 --> 00:44:51,520
He harms no soul,

627
00:44:52,200 --> 00:44:53,880
nor acts in a shady manner.

628
00:44:55,180 --> 00:44:55,840
Mm...

629
00:44:57,080 --> 00:44:58,400
I get it now. Continue.

630
00:44:59,960 --> 00:45:02,680
He seeks to devote every effort
toward the betterment of the land.

631
00:45:04,200 --> 00:45:05,000
Like doing work?

632
00:45:05,520 --> 00:45:06,280
What work?

633
00:45:07,040 --> 00:45:09,360
He serves in the ranks of
the Royal Patrol Division

634
00:45:09,620 --> 00:45:11,680
of the Ministry of the Capital.

635
00:45:13,420 --> 00:45:15,640
Cease this.
What manner of quarrel is this?

636
00:45:16,060 --> 00:45:18,240
Oh, so he's kinda like security?

637
00:45:19,460 --> 00:45:22,480
He safeguards the populace

638
00:45:23,340 --> 00:45:26,560
and suppresses
all manner of banditry and vice.

639
00:45:27,320 --> 00:45:28,400
He is indebted to us...

640
00:45:28,980 --> 00:45:30,400
the gambling debt, my Lord.

641
00:45:31,080 --> 00:45:33,280
Yet, your grievances
do not excuse this brawling.

642
00:45:34,220 --> 00:45:35,000
Leave.

643
00:45:36,020 --> 00:45:37,240
Claim your recompense on the morrow.

644
00:45:42,160 --> 00:45:43,200
Forsake the wager,

645
00:45:44,180 --> 00:45:45,720
and dedicate yourself to honest trade.

646
00:45:47,100 --> 00:45:48,760
Deliver unto them
the payment on the morrow.

647
00:45:49,360 --> 00:45:52,760
Oh, he's been working so hard

648
00:45:53,160 --> 00:45:54,560
that he doesn't have time for dating.

649
00:45:56,180 --> 00:45:56,640
I mean...

650
00:45:57,260 --> 00:45:58,000
Seeking a partner.

651
00:46:00,240 --> 00:46:01,680
You might well put it that way, indeed.

652
00:46:02,640 --> 00:46:03,960
The Lord usually

653
00:46:04,640 --> 00:46:05,680
takes no heed

654
00:46:06,460 --> 00:46:07,480
of the welfare of others.

655
00:46:10,980 --> 00:46:12,480
His concern is reserved solely for...

656
00:46:13,120 --> 00:46:14,640
you, Master Klao.

657
00:46:17,500 --> 00:46:18,680
Indeed, Master.

658
00:46:19,480 --> 00:46:21,800
In your absence,

659
00:46:22,240 --> 00:46:24,320
the Lord summoned us all
for a stern interrogation;

660
00:46:24,860 --> 00:46:26,440
his voice resounded across the estate.

661
00:46:28,380 --> 00:46:29,920
Mm... I saw that.

662
00:46:31,220 --> 00:46:32,440
If that is the case, Master,

663
00:46:33,220 --> 00:46:35,120
do not depart from us again,

664
00:46:36,160 --> 00:46:37,800
for I fear the Lord
may fall into worry once more.

665
00:46:50,800 --> 00:46:52,120
To regain one's memory

666
00:46:52,720 --> 00:46:54,320
requires a long period of restoration.

667
00:46:55,300 --> 00:46:56,960
I cannot say with certainty how long.

668
00:47:00,640 --> 00:47:04,000
Yet you are the finest curer
the capital has ever known.

669
00:47:04,800 --> 00:47:07,280
Surely some remedy exists
to aid his recovery.

670
00:47:08,000 --> 00:47:09,480
I accept your praise with gratitude.

671
00:47:10,780 --> 00:47:12,640
Yet whichever curer you consult,

672
00:47:13,780 --> 00:47:15,000
the conclusion remains immutable.

673
00:47:18,140 --> 00:47:20,440
I shall provide
a remedy to strengthen the mind, then.

674
00:47:23,780 --> 00:47:25,560
Shall we see to him at the manor?

675
00:47:25,820 --> 00:47:26,520
I concur,

676
00:47:27,480 --> 00:47:28,640
though only on the morrow.

677
00:47:29,830 --> 00:47:31,120
The capital calls this day.

678
00:47:32,040 --> 00:47:33,000
The capital?

679
00:47:33,900 --> 00:47:35,000
Who requires your summons?

680
00:47:40,820 --> 00:47:42,880
I require the procurement of medicines
from the Farangi.

681
00:47:43,760 --> 00:47:45,320
No one summons me.

682
00:47:47,880 --> 00:47:49,360
Is another day agreeable to you?

683
00:47:50,660 --> 00:47:52,600
Klao's condition remains precarious.

684
00:47:53,880 --> 00:47:54,800
You...

685
00:47:55,200 --> 00:47:56,370
Regarding Klao's affairs,

686
00:47:56,400 --> 00:47:58,400
your heart is more troubled
than your own.

687
00:48:03,760 --> 00:48:05,440
Phop, the hour of joy calls!

688
00:48:07,220 --> 00:48:09,040
- Klao, stay!
- Klao, mind your footing!

689
00:48:12,060 --> 00:48:13,360
Masters.

690
00:48:13,640 --> 00:48:15,040
Be wary, Masters.

691
00:48:16,040 --> 00:48:17,080
Masters.

692
00:48:20,880 --> 00:48:22,800
Pursue me, if your legs are stout.

693
00:48:25,720 --> 00:48:26,560
Crash!

694
00:48:27,860 --> 00:48:29,560
Jom, this is for you.

695
00:48:30,180 --> 00:48:31,000
Away with it.

696
00:48:31,920 --> 00:48:32,880
I am no lady.

697
00:48:36,680 --> 00:48:37,530
- Master!
- Master!

698
00:48:37,560 --> 00:48:38,120
Klao!

699
00:48:38,420 --> 00:48:39,360
Master!

700
00:48:40,180 --> 00:48:41,200
Master...

701
00:48:44,120 --> 00:48:45,570
Klao, you are but a whimper.

702
00:48:45,600 --> 00:48:47,320
Seek solace in your lady mother's skirts.

703
00:48:54,100 --> 00:48:55,880
Jom, cease this mockery.

704
00:48:56,160 --> 00:48:57,600
Heed your manners.

705
00:48:58,280 --> 00:49:00,760
You know full well
he is bereft of a mother's care.

706
00:49:06,680 --> 00:49:08,330
We shall escort you to the manor, Master.

707
00:49:08,360 --> 00:49:09,040
Need not.

708
00:49:09,760 --> 00:49:10,400
I will attend to him.

709
00:49:31,400 --> 00:49:32,800
It is truly a grievous thing,

710
00:49:33,040 --> 00:49:34,600
to have been orphaned of a mother's love.

711
00:49:40,960 --> 00:49:41,760
Jom.

712
00:49:42,760 --> 00:49:43,840
I propose that

713
00:49:44,160 --> 00:49:45,840
we attend to him together.

714
00:49:46,400 --> 00:49:48,960
I have prepared
his beloved dessert, khanom tom.

715
00:49:49,400 --> 00:49:51,320
Attend to him swiftly,
before the freshness fades.

716
00:49:54,700 --> 00:49:55,800
On the morrow.

717
00:49:56,800 --> 00:49:59,880
Your affections
have been so lavish that Klao is spoiled.

718
00:50:00,380 --> 00:50:02,120
Observe the fruits
of such lavish indulgence.

719
00:50:02,420 --> 00:50:04,040
To find his company, seek breweries

720
00:50:04,480 --> 00:50:05,520
and the ladies of the night.

721
00:50:05,730 --> 00:50:07,600
He is favored by fortune
to have found his way back.

722
00:50:09,480 --> 00:50:10,960
I have long felt the urge to caution him,

723
00:50:12,320 --> 00:50:14,160
but solely out of deference
to your feelings,

724
00:50:15,400 --> 00:50:17,440
I refrained from speaking.

725
00:50:32,280 --> 00:50:33,370
I am utterly confounded.

726
00:50:33,400 --> 00:50:35,680
You have forgotten how to wrap your attire,
or to take sustenance.

727
00:50:36,180 --> 00:50:38,620
At least you still retain
the ability to dine.

728
00:50:38,650 --> 00:50:40,000
Else, I fear for your very life.

729
00:50:44,940 --> 00:50:46,680
Master! Master!

730
00:50:47,500 --> 00:50:48,680
Your attire is disheveled.

731
00:50:49,560 --> 00:50:51,200
Allow me to assist you, Master.

732
00:50:51,380 --> 00:50:52,440
Come on.

733
00:50:53,060 --> 00:50:55,360
If you're not gonna let me wear my trousers,

734
00:50:55,480 --> 00:50:57,680
then let me wear them like this they're too tight.

735
00:50:58,400 --> 00:50:59,630
It cannot be done, Master.

736
00:50:59,660 --> 00:51:01,160
Grant me this one request, Master.

737
00:51:02,480 --> 00:51:04,240
- Allow me to assist you.
- Gosh.

738
00:51:05,080 --> 00:51:06,320
- Master Klao.
- Mm.

739
00:51:14,100 --> 00:51:15,570
What stays your hand, Chuay?

740
00:51:15,600 --> 00:51:16,760
The Lord has summoned you.

741
00:51:17,000 --> 00:51:18,920
Oh dear, he is summoning us.

742
00:51:20,860 --> 00:51:22,800
Make haste, for His Excellency awaits.

743
00:51:23,150 --> 00:51:24,200
As predicted.

744
00:51:24,300 --> 00:51:25,380
His Excellency awaits.

745
00:51:25,840 --> 00:51:27,960
Gosh, why did you have to repeat his words?

746
00:51:28,980 --> 00:51:29,920
Master.

747
00:51:30,420 --> 00:51:32,080
If you find the Lord stern,

748
00:51:32,600 --> 00:51:33,960
you shall find his father, His Excellency,

749
00:51:34,480 --> 00:51:35,760
even more formidable.

750
00:51:35,960 --> 00:51:37,080
I beg of you, Master.

751
00:51:37,420 --> 00:51:38,720
Attend to your attire, Master.

752
00:51:38,860 --> 00:51:40,920
Urgh. Come on, get up.

753
00:51:43,600 --> 00:51:44,440
Fine!

754
00:51:55,360 --> 00:51:56,280
Troubled throat?

755
00:52:21,980 --> 00:52:22,780
That is Kong,

756
00:52:23,780 --> 00:52:24,880
the Lord's servant.

757
00:52:38,400 --> 00:52:39,280
Hello.

758
00:52:43,980 --> 00:52:44,880
Hello?

759
00:52:46,680 --> 00:52:48,160
Do you speak a foreign tongue, Dear Klao?

760
00:52:48,460 --> 00:52:50,440
Or is that
the customary greeting of Phichit?

761
00:52:51,640 --> 00:52:52,400
Phichit...

762
00:52:53,160 --> 00:52:54,480
Klao's from Phichit?

763
00:52:55,440 --> 00:52:56,400
Be seated.

764
00:52:57,320 --> 00:52:58,600
Take your place beside Phop.

765
00:52:59,200 --> 00:52:59,920
Understood.

766
00:53:10,080 --> 00:53:11,920
Phop has mentioned your affliction.

767
00:53:12,500 --> 00:53:13,540
How fares your recovery?

768
00:53:14,880 --> 00:53:15,680
Has it taken its leave?

769
00:53:19,260 --> 00:53:20,720
The servants claim that

770
00:53:20,960 --> 00:53:22,200
you have gone mad.

771
00:53:22,940 --> 00:53:23,680
Is it so?

772
00:53:26,000 --> 00:53:27,600
Has your recollection entirely vanished?

773
00:53:27,640 --> 00:53:28,600
Good heavens.

774
00:53:29,800 --> 00:53:30,360
Who...

775
00:53:31,130 --> 00:53:32,010
Who am I?

776
00:53:33,360 --> 00:53:34,200
By what name am I known?

777
00:53:42,480 --> 00:53:43,520
Is your mind a complete void?

778
00:53:49,200 --> 00:53:51,800
It appears
he has not only lost his memories,

779
00:53:52,040 --> 00:53:54,440
but he has also
lost his command of language.

780
00:53:55,640 --> 00:53:57,120
Could this man truly not be Dear Klao?

781
00:53:59,720 --> 00:54:01,520
Is this an apparition cast in his likeness?

782
00:54:01,550 --> 00:54:02,640
- Oh...
- Oh.

783
00:54:02,920 --> 00:54:04,600
- Oh, dear.
- Go not near him.

784
00:54:07,100 --> 00:54:07,840
Bud.

785
00:54:08,520 --> 00:54:09,280
Euang.

786
00:54:11,120 --> 00:54:13,640
Cease your jesting for now.

787
00:54:15,960 --> 00:54:16,840
Dearest Klao,

788
00:54:17,780 --> 00:54:19,480
my name is Lady Prayong,

789
00:54:20,220 --> 00:54:21,600
Lord Phop's mother

790
00:54:22,860 --> 00:54:25,560
and the primary consort of
High Lord Pichayabhakdi.

791
00:54:28,200 --> 00:54:30,960
On the morrow, we shall visit the temple.

792
00:54:31,080 --> 00:54:32,600
Kindly join me on this journey

793
00:54:33,480 --> 00:54:36,280
so that misfortunes may be dispelled.

794
00:54:41,080 --> 00:54:42,360
The current moment is ill-suited,

795
00:54:44,100 --> 00:54:45,320
for he is still feeble.

796
00:54:46,280 --> 00:54:47,680
The Curer forbids his departure
from the estate.

797
00:54:48,400 --> 00:54:49,440
It is a journey to the temple.

798
00:54:49,720 --> 00:54:51,320
What harm could possibly befall him, Phop?

799
00:54:53,720 --> 00:54:54,560
Dearest Klao.

800
00:54:55,000 --> 00:54:56,320
Will you join our journey to the temple?

801
00:54:57,640 --> 00:54:58,360
With pleasure.

802
00:55:01,920 --> 00:55:02,840
Behold.

803
00:55:03,560 --> 00:55:04,720
This brings him immense joy.

804
00:55:05,800 --> 00:55:07,320
Abide by your mother's words.

805
00:55:08,240 --> 00:55:09,520
You, too, are to join us

806
00:55:10,520 --> 00:55:11,560
and accompany him.

807
00:55:12,600 --> 00:55:13,680
Understood, Father.

808
00:55:15,640 --> 00:55:18,350
It is my decree that
he vacate the small manor

809
00:55:18,380 --> 00:55:20,240
and take up residence here.

810
00:55:22,120 --> 00:55:23,520
It's okay.

811
00:55:26,880 --> 00:55:29,400
I'd rather stay at the small manor.

812
00:55:31,160 --> 00:55:32,320
I also don't want to trouble you.

813
00:55:34,200 --> 00:55:35,480
You shall seek shelter here,

814
00:55:36,080 --> 00:55:37,640
where your well-being
can be properly overseen.

815
00:55:38,760 --> 00:55:39,880
Prior to his passing,

816
00:55:40,760 --> 00:55:42,200
Lord Preechapiban,

817
00:55:42,420 --> 00:55:43,740
your father,

818
00:55:44,700 --> 00:55:46,040
left you in my keeping.

819
00:55:46,820 --> 00:55:48,240
Should you vanish once more,

820
00:55:49,200 --> 00:55:50,440
your father's spirit

821
00:55:50,920 --> 00:55:52,160
shall find no rest.

822
00:55:56,560 --> 00:55:57,320
Chuay.

823
00:55:57,800 --> 00:55:59,800
Retrieve your master's essential belongings

824
00:56:00,580 --> 00:56:02,120
and convey them here before nightfall.

825
00:56:03,200 --> 00:56:03,880
Yes, my Lord.

826
00:56:06,480 --> 00:56:07,960
Klao's father had already died.

827
00:56:08,920 --> 00:56:09,760
What was the cause of his death?

828
00:56:10,900 --> 00:56:13,640
Why did he leave Klao with His Excellency?

829
00:56:21,440 --> 00:56:22,680
Everyone's staring at me harshly.

830
00:56:23,120 --> 00:56:23,880
Why?

831
00:56:24,680 --> 00:56:25,320
Gosh.

832
00:56:25,600 --> 00:56:27,440
How am I supposed to pretend to be him?

833
00:56:27,840 --> 00:56:29,600
I know nothing about Klao.

834
00:56:39,160 --> 00:56:40,720
Our current proximity is indeed ideal,

835
00:56:43,400 --> 00:56:45,680
for it allows me
to keep a close eye on you.

836
00:56:46,920 --> 00:56:48,120
Isn't this a bit weird?

837
00:56:48,260 --> 00:56:50,760
Are you sure
we're just friends from childhood?

838
00:56:51,640 --> 00:56:53,280
This freaking Lord...

839
00:56:53,520 --> 00:56:55,240
What is he to Klao?

840
00:57:09,600 --> 00:57:10,600
Do eat.

841
00:57:11,180 --> 00:57:12,560
You have withered in our absence.

842
00:57:21,800 --> 00:57:22,840
Don't tell me...

843
00:57:23,840 --> 00:57:25,280
Don't tell me that...

844
00:57:27,560 --> 00:57:30,560
Help!!

845
00:57:51,600 --> 00:57:52,560
Father!

846
00:57:52,860 --> 00:57:54,360
Klao's father is dead.

847
00:57:54,880 --> 00:57:56,680
Whose voice roars so loudly yonder?

848
00:57:57,440 --> 00:57:58,360
Fortune teller!

849
00:57:58,400 --> 00:57:59,240
Klao!

850
00:57:59,480 --> 00:58:01,160
You ought not to run about on your own.

851
00:58:01,190 --> 00:58:03,040
Someone might do you harm.

852
00:58:03,400 --> 00:58:04,600
You are the one

853
00:58:04,600 --> 00:58:05,620
who harms me.

854
00:58:06,320 --> 00:58:08,800
Suffers from amnesia
and remembers nothing of himself...

855
00:58:09,000 --> 00:58:12,000
Should I ever forget you,
what will you do?

856
00:58:12,100 --> 00:58:13,600
Nothing.

857
00:58:13,680 --> 00:58:15,170
Even if you forget me,

858
00:58:15,200 --> 00:58:16,680
I shall care for you still.

859
00:58:17,600 --> 00:58:19,200
I told you not to come in yet, Chuay.

860
00:58:21,900 --> 00:58:23,120
Forgive me for this morning.

861
00:58:25,160 --> 00:58:26,400
Do not hold it against me.

862
00:58:32,280 --> 00:58:37,170
♫Seeing you feels like destiny come true♫

863
00:58:37,200 --> 00:58:42,240
♫All that I dream and long for leads to you♫

864
00:58:42,240 --> 00:58:46,920
♫Fate isn't chance, but something meant to be♫

865
00:58:46,920 --> 00:58:52,200
♫Thank you for giving love its meaning to me♫

866
00:58:52,200 --> 00:58:57,200
♫Seeing you now is more than fantasy♫

867
00:58:57,200 --> 00:59:02,120
♫Every second I give you faithfully♫

868
00:59:02,150 --> 00:59:08,080
♫As time goes on, no matter where we are♫

869
00:59:08,110 --> 00:59:15,900
♫My heart is yours, no matter near or far♫

870
00:59:25,640 --> 00:59:29,520
[Love Upon a Time Series]

